                        <p>The letter consists of 7 sheets of paper with typewriting on each side. There are several smudge
                            marks from where the typist tried to erase a letter or word. On page 6, there is a big piece of the
                            left side torn out that cuts off some of the words on the back of that page, page 7. Also on page 7
                            is two lines that are typed over each other. Page eight has a word at the bottom that is scratched
                            out with pen or pencil instead of using an eraser. On the top of each sheet of paper (aka every
                            other page) is a page number.</p> 
